\f0\fs24 \cf0 # CODEX ADDENDUM \'97 FAA AD AUTO-TRACKING + REMINDERS IS REQUIRED\
\
This addendum is mandatory.\
\
## Existing product truth\
The system already has:\
- aircraft records\
- reminders\
- customer/org context\
- FAA aircraft lookup foundations\
\
Therefore users should NOT have to manually hunt for all ADs for an aircraft already inside the platform.\
\
## Build requirement\
Whenever an aircraft exists or is created/updated:\
1. derive applicability profile from aircraft data\
2. sync FAA AD source records in the background\
3. determine likely applicable ADs\
4. store aircraft-specific AD status\
5. create/update reminders automatically\
6. link maintenance-entry evidence to AD compliance when found\
7. recompute due/overdue state on every new evidence ingestion\
\
## Reminder integration requirements\
Use existing reminders infrastructure where possible.\
Add reminder categories/types for:\
- ad_unknown_compliance\
- ad_due_soon\
- ad_overdue\
- recurring_ad_due\
- annual_due\
- 100hr_due\
- transponder_due\
- elt_due\
- static_system_due\
- vor_due\
\
## Aircraft page requirements\
Add / enhance:\
- AD summary widget\
- due soon / overdue / unknown counts\
- reminders panel\
- compliance evidence links\
- last sync status\
- sync now action\
- manual applicability override\
- manual compliance override\
- audit trail\
\
## Search requirements\
Users must be able to search:\
- ad:94-05-05\
- all ADs for aircraft\
- overdue ADs\
- AD references found in logbooks\
- evidence supporting compliance\
\
## Background job requirements\
- on aircraft create/update: sync applicability\
- on maintenance entry creation: recompute linked AD state\
- nightly: refresh FAA source + recompute reminders\
- on document completion: detect newly found AD evidence\
\
## Engineering honesty\
If the FAA source is imperfect, ambiguous, or not fully machine-readable:\
- keep source abstraction clean\
- normalize data carefully\
- expose uncertainty\
- never claim compliance without evidence}